result.execSummary:
The defendant Alfredo Alanis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Obstruct Highway w/ Embankment/Ditch, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 86.022.
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:27 AM Defendant Alfredo Alanis in court, in custody.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Carly June Sebion in court for Alfredo Alanis. Defendant pleading to Counts  2 - No Contest, 3 - No Contest & 4 - No Contest. Ct 1 DRI. 22TR128  case tracking dismissed and read in. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Ct 2 - Resisting or Obstructing an Officer contrary to 946.41(1), Ct 3 -  Obstruct Highway w/ Embankment/Ditch contrary to 86.0222, Ct 4 - Possession of THC contrary to 961.41(3g)(e). Defendant exercised his right to allocution. 

Joint recommendation: Counts 2 & 4, penalty of 9 months jail, find time served. Count 3, $10.00 fine plus costs. 214 days credit

Court adopts joint recommendation: Count 2, orders 9 month jail & Count 4, orders 6 months jail, concurrent. Finds time served. Court costs. Count 3, orders $10.00 fine plus costs. 214 days credit. 
Payment plan of $50.00 month granted, first payment due Nov 1, 2022, paying each month thereafter until paid in full.  

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.
